mparison, the commonly applied 2-3 σ clipping of the hard-band light curve misses a significant number of flares, rendering the temperatures beyond r=10' unconstrained. Thus, the background uncertainties do not prohibit the EPIC temperature profile analysis of low-brightness regions, such as outer regions of galaxy clusters, provided a conservative flare filtering such as the double-filtering method with +/-20\% limits is used.},
